<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                        <head>316. Telegram 1003 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d316fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/10–2655.
                                Official Use Only; Priority. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-10-26">October 26, 1955, 12:29
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d316-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d316-1"/>
                        <p>1003. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Your 962.</p>
                        <p>Defense unable supply specific information requested your 871 from
                            Washington files. Have asked Army to have search made of more complete
                            files stored Kansas City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH_1"><hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>